The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Thursday, January 09, 2003 				 Mamata boost to Friday bandh
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 																								Calcutta, Jan. 8: The Party for Democratic Socialism (PDS) today seemed optimistic about the success of the dawn-to-dusk bandh it has called on Friday against the misrule of the Left Front after Mamata Banerjee publicly pitched for the strike.																								Fridays bandh will be spontaneous since it is aimed at addressing some of the burning issues facing the people, said PDS chief Saifuddin Chowdhury. 																								The PDS, a breakaway group of the CPM, has called the bandh in protest against the increase in court fees, water tax and deteriorating law and order situation in the state.
